---
// Philosophy / How I Build Systems section
---

<section id="philosophy" class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 section-spacing reveal">
  <h2 class="h2-divider text-3xl tracking-tight">Engineering Principles</h2>
  <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <article class="card-premium p-8 reveal">
      <h3 class="flex items-start gap-3 text-base font-semibold">
        <span class="text-lg text-teal-400">01</span>
        Architecture First
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">API-driven design, clean service boundaries, and modular Laravel structures that scale.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card-premium p-8 reveal">
      <h3 class="flex items-start gap-3 text-base font-semibold">
        <span class="text-lg text-teal-400">02</span>
        Performance Mindset
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Measure first, optimize second. Frontend performance and backend resiliency are non-negotiable.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card-premium p-8 reveal">
      <h3 class="flex items-start gap-3 text-base font-semibold">
        <span class="text-lg text-teal-400">03</span>
        Product-Oriented
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">I build with users in mind—balancing technical excellence with business impact.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card-premium p-8 reveal">
      <h3 class="flex items-start gap-3 text-base font-semibold">
        <span class="text-lg text-teal-400">04</span>
        Long-Term Maintainability
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Readable code, strong validation layers, and systems designed for future teams.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
